4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT ESTABLISHING SAFE STAFFING STANDARDS FOR NURSES;
5 CREATING NURSE STAFFING COMMITTEES IN HOSPITALS TO PROTECT AND ENHANCE THE SAFETY
6 AND QUALITY OF PATIENT CARE; AND PRESCRIBING MINIMUM NURSE-TO-PATIENT RATIOS.”
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
9
10 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Nurse staffing plan -- hospital staffing committee -- report to
11 department. (1) Each hospital licensed by the department of public health and human services shall, in
12 coordination with its staffing committee as required in subsection (2), develop a nurse staffing plan that
13 promotes a collaborative hospital practice and enhances patient care. The safe nurse staffing plan must:
14 (a) prescribe the minimum professional nurse skill mix for each patient care unit in the hospital,
15 including:
16 (i) the ratio of patients to registered nurses providing direct patient care for each unit, which must
17 meet the minimum nurse-to-patient ratios prescribed in [section 2];
18 (ii) a description of any differences between the staffing levels prescribed in the staffing plan and
19 actual staffing levels for each unit, how the hospital intends to meet the staffing levels prescribed in the nurse
20 staffing plan, and whether the hospital will adjust staffing levels in future staffing plans;
21 (iii) the method used by the hospital to determine and adjust direct patient care nurse staffing
22 levels; and
23 (iv) a description of supporting personnel assisting in each patient care unit;
24 (b) identify the hospital's employment practices concerning the use of temporary and traveling
25 nurses;
26 (c) establish the hospital's process for internal review of the nurse staffing plan, including review
27 by the staffing committee, and any other review;
28 (d) identify how the hospital and its staffing committee receive input from direct care staff, including
