1 nurses and other members of the hospital's patient care team, in the development of the nurse staffing plan;
2 (e) be updated annually by the staffing committee; and
3 (f) receive majority approval of the staffing committee.
4 (2) (a) Each hospital licensed by the department shall establish a staffing committee to prepare
5 and approve by majority vote the nurse staffing plan required in subsection (1).
6 (b) (i) At least 50% of the membership of a staffing committee must consist of registered nurses
7 employed by the hospital in nonsupervisory roles and whose primary responsibility is to provide direct patient
8 care.
9 (ii) Except as provided in subsection (c), for hospitals in which nurses are represented through
10 collective bargaining, the collective bargaining agent shall select the members prescribed in subsection
11 (2)(b)(i).
12 (c) If a hospital has an existing committee whose membership consists of at least 50% registered
13 nurses who are employed by the hospital and whose primary responsibility is to provide direct patient care, the
14 hospital may designate that committee as the hospital's staffing committee.
15 (3) Each hospital licensed by the department shall post in each care unit a copy of the hospital’s
16 nurse staffing plan in a location that is visible, conspicuous, and accessible to staff, patients, and the public.
17 (4) (a) Each hospital licensed by the department shall maintain accurate records of the ratios of
18 direct care registered nurses to patients in each unit for each shift, including:
19 (i) the number of patients in each unit on each shift;
20 (ii) the number of direct care registered nurses assigned to each patient in each unit on each shift;
21 and
22 (iii) the number of supporting personnel in each unit on each shift.
23 (b) The records of the ratios of direct care registered nurses to patients must be available to the
24 hospital staff, the staff's collective bargaining agents, the patients, the general public, and the department on
25 request.
26 (5) Each hospital licensed by the department shall submit to the department annually its nurse
27 staffing plan with a written certification that the plan provides adequate and appropriate delivery of health care
28 services.
